tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.9%), indicating prediabetes. Renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are unremarkable. Recommend lifestyle modification and follow-up of glycemic status to prevent progression to diabetes. No acute laboratory concerns at this time.
